Package edu.missouri.drone.cooperative

This package includes all implemented algorithms for cooperative drone teams, such as those considered in REU 2020.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AngelMultiLayer
    This is Angel Flores' implentation of a cooperative, density-aware drone coverage procedure.
    BFSSadatDrone
    This is an implementation of Sadat et al.'s breadth-first-search coverage algorithm, where a single, very high-altitude image is taken of the whole region, then that region is split into smaller rectangular subregions, with subregions containing no objects according to the initial image ignored.
    CooperativeBFSDrone
    This is an implementation of Sadat et al.'s breadth-first-search coverage algorithm, where a single, very high-altitude image is taken of the whole region, then that region is split into smaller rectangular subregions, with subregions containing no objects according to the initial image ignored.
    CooperativeLayerDrone
    This is an implementation of the "layer" multi-drone strategy: one subteam of drones is responsible for high-altitude imagery, while another subteam directly visits possible objects found by the high-altitude subteam.
    DFSSadatDrone
    This is an implementation of the depth-first version of Sadat et al.
    EndToEndDirectDrone
    This class describes a coverage procedure where a number of drones split a path that a hypothetical drone with energy reserves equal to the sum of the group would take.
    EndToEndPlowSetDrone
    This class describes a coverage procedure where a number of drones split a path that a hypothetical drone with energy reserves equal to the sum of the group would take.
    HotspotterDrone
    HotspotterDrone is an implementation of a height-variant, object-density-aware cooperative drone.
    VertexPlowSetDrone
    This class describes a cooperative coverage approach where an area is split by vertices and each
